<h2>Projects</h2>
<ul>
	<li>Local and Global Optimizations Based on LLVM (<strong>C++</strong>), course project, Jan 2014
		<ul>
			<li>Local optimizations on basic blocks with constant folding, strength reduction, etc.
			<li>Global optimizations on modules using iterative data-flow analysis.
		</ul>
<p></p>
	<li>Bayou Protocol Implementation(<strong>Java</strong>), course project, Dec 2013
		<ul>
			<li>Implement the anti-entropy to support eventual consistency in asynchronous distributed systems.
		</ul>
<p></p>
	<li>Paxos Protocol Optimization(<strong>Java</strong>), course project, Nov 2013
		<ul>
			<li>Add failure detector in Paxos for asynchronous distributed systems to avoid potential large delay.
			<li>Optimize the read operation for Paxos to reduce the cost while guarantee consensus.
			<li>Apply Paxos into a bank application.
		</ul>
<p></p>
	<li>Three Phase Commit Protocol Implementation(<strong>Java</strong>), course project, Oct 2013
		<ul>
			<li>Implement a 3PC protocol for distributed recovery and atomic commit.
			<li>Support both partial failures and total failures.
		</ul>
<p></p>
	<li>Advanced-level Compiler Design(<strong>C++</strong>), course project, Fall 2011
		<ul>
			<li>Design and Complete a compiler from scratch, which transforms Pascal code into Win32 Assembly.
			<li>Peephole optimization, elimination of common subexpressions by DAG, heuristic graph coloring algorithm and assignments of the local and global registers.
		</ul>
<p></p>
	<li>Advanced-level Network Experiment(<strong>C++</strong>), course project, Spring 2012
		<ul>
			<li>Design and Implement a lightweight system for the OSPF (Open Shortest Path First) protocol.
		</ul>
<p></p>
</ul>
